<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-99] Lustre quotas are not directory based, but the Ops Manual indicates that they are</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-99</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Section 21.1 &quot;Working with Quotas&quot; of the Ops Manual begins, &quot;Quotas allow a system administrator to limit the amount of disk space a user or group can use in a &lt;em&gt;directory&lt;/em&gt;.&quot; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;emphasis mine&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, Lustre quotas are not directory based and this statement leads to confusion.  This minor issue can be resolved by deleting &quot;in a directory&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
